## SECTION 1 - DESIGN PHILOSOPHY & FAILURE MODES ADDRESSED

### **1.1 What This Architecture Solves**
Version 1.0 of the AGS plan had strong instincts but critical structural gaps. This document resolves every one of them with concrete mechanical solutions - not descriptions of intent.

| **V1 Weakness**                      | **Root Cause**                                              | **V2 Mechanical Fix**                                                                                    |
| ------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Confidence score as truth            | LLMs are miscalibrated - hallucinate at high confidence     | Schema-constrained output validation + tool-call parse guards replace self-reported confidence           |
| Failure Memory matched exact strings | Error signatures vary; same mistake, different library name | Embedding-based fuzzy match on error signatures using `sentence-transformers` stored in **ChromaDB**           |
| Persona Engine had no mechanism      | Names assigned to features, not to distinct agent configs   | Each persona = unique system prompt + model + tool allowlist + routing classifier rule                   |
| Ngrok as prod infra                  | Session-based tunnels expire; not HA                        | Cloudflare Tunnel (persistent) for local, Traefik for Docker/Cloud; Ngrok retained only for dev mode     |
| No rollback strategy                 | Dry-run passing did not guarantee execution safety          | Two-phase commit: dry-run diff → checksum snapshot → execute → verify; auto-revert on checksum mismatch  |
| No LLM API rate-limit handling       | Only web scraping had backoff                               | Token-bucket rate limiter in LLM Provider Proxy with per-provider quotas and automatic failover          |
| No orchestrator crash recovery       | If orchestrator dies mid-DAG, tasks are orphaned            | DAG state machine persisted to SQLite with WAL mode; restart resumes from last committed checkpoint      |
| Cost/latency unmodeled               | Every action routed through full critic pipeline            | Three-tier action classification: TRIVIAL (no critic), STANDARD (local critic), CRITICAL (full pipeline) |

