## SECTION 6 - MULTI-PROVIDER LLM PROXY (Rate Limiter)
All agent invocations go through `LLMProviderProxy`. This decouples persona definitions from provider availability. Redis stores token-bucket state per provider. When a bucket exhausts, proxy routes automatically (e.g. Local Ollama Exhausted -> Target Colab Ollama Endpoint).

| **Provider** | **Use Case** | **Failover Priority** |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Ollama (local)** | Default for all agents. | 1 (primary) |
| **Ollama (Colab)** | Activated by Bheem for heavy tasks. | 2 (compute overflow) |
| **Anthropic API** | Itachi, Madara, Ichigo, Ben 10. | 3 (quality escalation) |
| **OpenAI API** | Fallback if Anthropic blocked. | 4 (secondary cloud) |

